dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Saffron Walden, drift, sheet 205
dct_description_sm: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 205 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 52.183300. South Decimal Degree 52.0167. East Decimal Degree 0.4667. West Decimal Degree 0.0500. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological survey on the one-inch scale by W. H. Penning et al. Published on the Old Series sheets 47, 51 S.W. and 51 S.E. in 1881 and 1882; a drift edition of 47 in 1884. Re-surveyed in part on the six-inch scale in 1930-1 by H. G. Dines et al. Transferred to the New Series map with corrections, and published 1932.".
dct_publisher_sm: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1932.
